Business Brief -- Chips  Technologies Inc.:
   Firm Expects to Post Loss;
   Plans Layoffs, Consolidation
The San Jose, Calif., semiconductor company has already
slashed its work force through layoffs and attrition by 10%
to 656 employees since last summer. By March 1, the company
said it hopes to reduce its work force by another 100 to 200
employees. Chips also said it is establishing a reserve fund
of $16 million to $20 million to cover excess and slow-moving
inventory.